Description:
Stylish renovation, central location
$350,000-$380,000
Move right in, rent right out, secure your future in this fully renovated, wonderfully secure apartment. With undercover parking & intercom entry beyond auto-gates, this 1st-floor apartment makes the most of its quiet rear position with a touch of luxury. Step beyond a glossy front door to find parquet- floored living flowing out to a private balcony, fresh carpets through 2 robe-fitted bedrooms & the comfort of reverse-cycle air-conditioning. Styled up with a sophisticated Blanco appliance kitchen & sleek fully-tiled bathroom with private WC & laundry facilities, this deluxe apartment has style to adore ...with a location owner-occupiers & tenants alike will love near Ormond station & shops.
robes in both bedrooms, designer bathroom
balcony, parquet-floors, rev-cyc air-con
covered parking behind auto-gates, intercom
leafy location 1 block to Ormond station

Description:
Pretty, picturesque & positioned in Zone!
$580,000-$630,000
Pretty, period & positioned in the College Zone, this charming single-fronted home maximises its perfectly-sized grounds with a carport out front & a 2nd storey above. Extended to offer 3 bedroom, 2 bathroom accommodation, this stylish home has richly stained floorboards flowing from a gasfire-warmed lounge into sunlit casual living with glass ceiling. Centrally heated, reverse-cycle air-conditioned & alarmed, there's an elegant bathroom on each level & a way to step out upstairs & down - with a curvaceous deck from ground-floor living & a pretty balcony from the 3rd bedroom. 2 blocks to Ormond station & shops & a walk to the College, this is a pretty perfect entry to the Zone.
3 bedrooms with robes, bathroom on each level
formal & casual living areas, classic kitchen
duct heating, rev-cyc air-con, alarm, carport
desirable College Zone address, near station

Description:
Hidden treasure in a Hill court
$750,000-$790,000
Find your very own country-style hideaway ...right in the McKinnon College Zone & right on top of Ormond Hill! Tucked away at the end of a secluded cul-de-sac beyond a wide & welcoming approx 57ft frontage, this 3 bedroom, 2 bathroom charmer has the Primary School at the door, bountiful gardens all around & endless north-sun across the rear. Appreciate this picturesque home for its flexible floorplan with L-shaped living wrapping a pretty kitchen with dishwasher, a rear sun-room & versatile family-room ready to double as a vast 4th bedroom beside a dedicated bathroom...or appreciate the potential to create a luxurious new home to crown the end of this covetable court

$290,000-$320,000
Start, invest or empty nest - when you choose this exciting entry to leafy Lillimur, it's all in front of you. Set to the front on the first-floor in this fast-developing street of quality homes & unit developments, this well-presented 2 bedroom apartment has been polished up with glossy hardwood timber floors, cosied up with a warm solid-timber kitchen & opened up with wide windows from each bedroom onto the tree-lined street outside. With carport parking secured behind auto gates adding peace of mind, & a great location just off the Ormond shopping strip & just two blocks to the station adding easy amenity, this up-front, up-high apartment is the perfect start-up!

Description:
City Sparkle & A Design That Shines!
Come out on top with a smart floorplan and sparkling view! Top floor on the edge of the Ormond shopping strip, this exceptional apartment offers cleverly designed two bedroom, two bathroom accommodation, McKinnon College Zoning and a distant view of the CBD lights.
Carefully thought out to offer dual suite accommodation, this spacious apartment
features main bedroom with a dedicated ensuite plus another granite-finished bathroom beside the second bedroom, perfect for privacy... and ideal for sharehousing!
Living space is equally well-designed with open-plan living/dining flowing around a sophisticated granite kitchen and out to a wide balcony for the best aspect on the city skyline.
With a lack of upstairs neighbours enhancing the peace, and two carspaces plus secure storage in basement garaging enhancing peace-of-mind, this high quality apartment is high on extras too. There's reverse-cycle air-conditioning supplemented by panel heating, secure intercom entry and European appliances as well as a discreet European laundry.
High on top of the world with station, shops and restaurants at the door and the College within a walk, there's no better place to take a new view!
Sophorn En : 0402 149 342

Description:
RUN RUN RUN AS FAST AS YOU CAN...
...to get this fabulous 2 bedroom, 1st floor apartment in a security block. Comprising entrance hall, renovated kitchen with adjoining tiled meals area, a good size lounge room with air conditioning and loads of natural light.
The master bedroom is a great size, also making use of the natural light, has a whole wall dedicated to robes with top storage area and is complemented with quality carpets and drapes. The 2nd bedroom has double robes and is south facing.
Other features in this 'can not be missed' apartment are bathroom with washing machine facilities and bath, very rare in an apartment. Communal laundry, intercom security system, carport and automatic gates. All this and just a short stroll to station and shops!!!

Description:
Californian grace, family space
$780,000-$850,000
Pretty, picket-fenced & set in a period-perfect streetscape, this 3 bedroom Californian Bungalow has been renovated & extended with a clever mix of traditional flair & contemporary verve. In formal lounge & dining rooms timber floors & a beautiful fireplace are the focus, while a timeless tiled family zone extends a classic black & white scheme to a CaesarStone & St George appliance kitchen. With a separate powder-room for the skylit bathroom, dining-sized decking for the big backyard & ducted heating & evaporative cooling, this quality renovation has all the comforts - there's parking behind gates for at least 3 cars (including a garage) & an 3100L tank to keep gardens gorgeously healthy.

Description:
In-Zone beauty with scope
$650,000-$710,000
Respectfully renovated & artfully styled, this solid-brick c.1929 home is a divine Deco in the desirable McKinnon College Zone. Beyond dual leadlight doors, this gracious 3 bedroom home showcases glossy hardwood floors & elaborate ceilings across a grand plan with interconnected formal rooms featuring an impressive fireplace. But it's not all about period grace - beneath a cathedral ceiling, a modern casual area flows from timeless timber kitchen (with Smeg cooktop) to covered decking in lush gardens. With ducted heating, alarm, almost 4,000L of water-storage & 2-car auto-garage with workshop, this is the ideal place to enjoy Zone life ...with perfect potential to extend up or out.
3 bedrooms, classic bathroom, powder-rm
3,700L water store & deck in gorgeous gardens
2-car garage & workshop, duct-htg, alarm
